76561198054903559,Recommended,278910,28165496,"Posted: 3 December, 2016",all,bonaccorsi,"Interplanetary is a physics oriented artillery space game. It's a turn-based game, first you need to manage your home planet and set the shots, and then you sit and see in real time the combat between the planets.I really enjoyed to set the trajectory of your guns against the enemy planets - they move around a star, and the gravity affect all the shots (except the lasers).I also liked the management of the buildings on your home planet: you need to connect them with energy supplies, defend them with support structures, etc. If you shot with lasers and missiles weapons, you can also choose the targets on the desired enemy planet.This game also features a tech tree, with lots of new techonlogies that improve your civilization.There's a in-game text tutorial window, very clear about how to play, and I had no trouble entering directly into the action.The only think I dislike was that sometimes the AI takes too much to think about his actions, but it's not a big deal.I am having a great fun playing this game, I recommend for the playes who like strategy and physics games."
