,Recommended,278910,11204067,"Posted: 12 July, 2014",all,Dead Rising 2,"This game has a near infinite amount of replayability, and a near infinite amount of play styles. Sometimes people will bombard your planet with railgun shots on the second turn, and sometimes no shots will be fired until somebody calls in an asteroid. The tech tree fits the length of the game perfectly, as well as it is almost 100% balanced. The new upgrade feature really adds another dimension to the optimal play-style, as it allows for more energy and materials to be produced in a smaller area. The array of weapons that you can arm your planet with is grand, be it with pinpoint accuracy lasers or homing missiles. One of the best, but most complicated parts of the combat system is the gravity of the planets and the sun. You could aim a shot so that it looks like it will be spot on, but then the planets will orbit and gravity will throw the shot out of the system. All in all, this game was definately a 10/10, I hope to see many new features in the future."
