76561198016739532,Recommended,278910,15826294,"Posted: 14 May, 2015",all,Chaser Zulu,"So, as someone who's versed with orbital mechanics (OM) and ""similar things"", this naturally caught my eye.  Bottom line up front:  good game with a lot of potential.  It's worth a look if you dig this sort of stuff.Yes, ""a lot of potential"" means it's not quite there yet.  Stop right there if you're thinking, ""Yeah but it's early access.""  Early access should entice the gamer to want more, not frustrate with a product that they won't want even when it's complete.   Even science fiction has a logic that binds it together to make it believable in its own realm.  I've pounded my adversary round after round only for the AI to win and destroy all my cities in the last round.  This looks like an inadvertent cop-out from the designers that should be addressed.  The OM/physics needs work.  I've done OM related work before...we're familiar with heavenly bodies and gravitational fields.  The projected trajectory is a cool concept but we can predict with great accuracy where an object will go.  A civilization that can launch stuff as easily into orbit surely would have better OM capabilities as well (not eyeball it).  I get that the trajectory aiming is part of the game, but when my shots go awry...it doesn't give this player the ""hmm I didn't think of that.""  A few of my shots very closely mimicked the AI's trajectory.  The AI ended perfectly on target while mine was influenced by a mysterious force (note inadvertent cop-out statement).  IMHO, the game play needs more polishing to reach the ""intuitive controls"" level.  They aren't hard figure out, but there's no good explanation as to what does what and why it does it.  For example, there's no clear reason as to choose certain research projects in the tech tree.  Do they make a worthwhile difference?  How will the designers show this to the players in the upgrades to come?I'm content with this purchase.  But I'm an easy guy to please.  And if I'm merely content, I'm quite certain the majority of players are expecting that the ""best of Interplanetary is yet to come.""  I for one will be expecting that as well.  At this point, I recommend the game...with the cautionary wink and smile."
