,Recommended,278910,10660079,"Posted: 22 June, 2014",all,ToxiGhost,"Note: This review was written during early access meaning things may change as more patches are released.It's dfficult for me to recommend this game right now despite the fact that I love it, since it's primarily a multiplayer experience and i've only managed to get into one game with other players since buying it a month ago. The server lobby is often empty and hosting a game takes quite a while most times as you wait for players to join.With that being said, if you don't mind waiting 10 minutes or so to fill an online game lobby, or you simply want to play LAN with a friend or family member, I think it's a really enjoyable experience all round with a very solid feel to the game.Your goal is to develop your planet in a relatively simple sense, then stick some guns onto it and take aim at your opponent's planets. It sounds easy, but considoring gravity pulls on all weapons, aiming can be very tricky at long ranges until you get the hang of it! But it's not a frustrating kind of tricky, it's the kind that makes you shout ""YEEEEAH!!!! WOO!"" when you get a hit and read the damage report.The game is turn based.Graphically this game is pretty sexy looking with a simple UI and good quality chat window.The community, atleast when you find other members of it, seem really great. A playful, fun loving and intelligent bunch from my experience so far.For the price, Interplanetary is well worth it (£4.99 at the time of writing this reviewm however don't expect to see thousands of players online waiting for a game and if you're not into using your head and patience as you game, it probably isn't for you, otherwise space and RTS fans alike will love this little gem :)Thanks for reading!"
