,Recommended,278910,9942582,"Posted: 26 April, 2014",all,misterbob,"This is a promising game with what's currently on offer, considering it's still early access. It's very pretty and the combat mechanics are a lot of fun, trying to aim rockets to curve around other objects in the solar system makes it a lot more entertaining than selecting a target and firing.The development of planets is pretty simple with only about 10 different types of buildings you can build. This is both a blessing and a curse; it makes the game easy to pick up and I was fairly familiar to the mechanics within a few hours, but of course for people who playa  lot of strategy games it might be overly simple. Most things currently in the game seem well balanced, with the possible exception of the ""super weapons"". They seem rather overpowered and from my experience, most rounds just end up as a race to be the first to get one.My online experience hasn't been great so far, I'm yet to complete a game online due to various issues with the game itself as well as people just dropping out of games. It's really disappointing because there is a lot of potential that isn't being found there yet. The non-online ""hotseat"" mode is a lot of fun as it stands and with private online matches or some sort of system to stop people dropping out (possibly reputation depending on how many games you finish?), the online multiplayer could be great too.There's no single player as it stands, but this is of course planned and could be really solid too, as long as the AI are up to scratch.In short, this game is good as it currently is, but I see the potential for it to be great, and at this price, who could argue with that?"
