76561198088641060,Recommended,278910,17858262,"Posted: 2 September, 2015",all,greenwood42,"Ok so I have played the computer a few times, and a couple of games against humans. I got to say this about Interplanetary: It is a very strategic game. You spend a lot of time pondering your next move, the tech tree is deep but not that deep, making your choices of tech dictate your strategy. Do you run gun spam? Get missles? Run for a super weapon... etc. Every turn your choices have a long term impact on your future, choose wisely. Its by far not a 'super' complex game, but its better that way. The amount of choices available allow make it not some wildely varying battle but a game of the mind. The price is right, not to expensive, and the game has supprising depth for something so viscerally appealing (you can't say the idea of bombarding your fellow planets doesn't appeal to you.) The graphics, sounds, and music are all good, and run fast on even simple machines. A must get for strat gamers everywhere."
