76561197972539767,Recommended,278910,16046334,"Posted: 28 May, 2015",all,Dr. Pilotneko,"I've always loved turn-based artillery action, and Interplanetary is a welcome addition to the genre. Less ""Worms"" and more ""Scorched Earth"" with some strategic building mixed in. Online play is where the game shines, although curiously online AI players are not yet supported.I would like to see a few additions/changes made, if possible.1) Persistent projectiles: Currently, if projectiles miss their targets, they explode before the next round starts. It would be nice if they remained until they hit something. This would add some much needed chaos and open up the possibility of new strategy elements (flood the solar system with cheap railgun slugs and hope for the best!).2) Balance for orbit positions: Some may disagree, but the players on the outer orbits are definitely at an advantage. Players on the inner orbits are guaranteed to get chewed up first, and the outer rim planets are free to build up and attain superweapons. Perhaps the method of balancing this would be my third suggestion...3) Planet speed: It seems that all of the planets move at the same speed, but the outer ones should move slower. This would make them easier to hit, perhaps?The developer seems to be actively updating the game, so hopefully they can consider these suggestions. All in all though, an amazing game! I highly recommend it!"
