76561198009447375,Recommended,278910,15900889,"Posted: 19 May, 2015",all,bluerat,"This game is the love child of Worms and the tabletop game Battleship ... but in space!! ><It is simply awesome ... play it, you won't regret it.In more detail, 3 pro's and 3 con's for balance:Pro's:1) it has the addictive charm of both the above mentioned games; as it utilizes the artillery style of worms with the damage style of Battleship. To win you have to eliminate your opponents cities, and in a few multiplayer games I've had opponents yelling ''i sunk your battleship'' ... which continues to make me smile.2) it is very simple to pick up, as the general mechanics and the buildings should make sense to you very quickly, and games are also relatively quick, so it's great for short bursts of fun - though mastering the game is not easy. There is also no story or general context, or diplomacy, other than to 'sink' those cities. That sounds bad but it is not, it is refreshing and the game excels at providing focused strategic fun.3) it is satisfying - hitting an opponent on a near impossible shot, or having your planet just escape a major hit ... it just feels good.Con's:1) not much information feedback from the game. it would be nice to know how much damage I did, or how many shots got through, or, well, anything really ... there is also no information at the end of the game either. I guess I could just be spoilt by other games, as this does not detract from the enjoyment or mechanics. However, even though I can understand that limited information is best at the end of each turn (that the intelligence system should give you what you need), there could be something at the very end (even a simplistic score based on damage or population or something).2) a bit buggy, had a few crashes here and there and the AI takes a while to make a turn.3) no quick save feature (as far as I can tell). Given the occasional crashes it is useful to save after each turn, which means going into the menu each time and selecting a save ... not a hassle you say? It gets really annoying after a while.Overall: just buy it and love it. My hopes are this game will continue to get developed, as I would love to see a few extra buildings, a bigger tech tree and all new features. It is addictive fun :)p.s: though the game is best played with other people, the AI seems fine to me. I've only played on easy and normal but the AI seems to generally hit well enough and miss well enough on both of those settings ... the AI is not obviously overpowered or underpowered to me, though they don't really use telescopes to spy on the player much."
