ing the amount of damage- map mode: 3d is really cool but later on you lose sight of whats where. offer the option to see your planet in 2d- ai turns randomly start taking forever which doesnt go away. this seems not related to how much buildings/weapons/resources the player has- circus shots: i get that the computer can calculate these but at least have them use routes that are the shortest path. its unexpectedly aggrevating seeing a missile flying two laps around the sun before hitting- after the first few playthroughs i feel like the orbits could be more random, maybe elliptical (not crossing), there could be more than one obstacle planet on the empty orbits, etc.- maybe events? maybe more things? i basically play the same first 6 turns because nothing else makes sensei  dont regret buying this game but will put it aside for now - hoping that a few updates down the road it becomes what it deserves to be. like it is now, its not worth the money."
